        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "The action view helper is mostly used totally wrong (I never knew any actual use-case for it). Instead of using view helpers or models, people start to use actions as reusable units. If there's actually a use-case for the action view helper, it should be mentioned in the documentation, for what it actually is for, else I'd suggest to remove it (in 2.0, to keep BC before), and probably yet mark it as deprecated (see ZF-8170)."
        },
