        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28944",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Though it fits perfectly in the use-at-will spirit of ZF, I do think that it costs way too much resources (as I recall right, it does an entire dispatch..), and asks for bad design. Therefore, let's get rid of it :D",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-02-19T08:26:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-28T11:51:39.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28961",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I agree.\nWe should still be able to use that helper if we want to.\nAnyway, regarding the performance problem, it *is* specified in the official doc, in the performance chapter, so anyone should know about it.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-02-20T00:52:50.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-02-20T00:52:50.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31440",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gnarf",
                        "name": "gnarf",
                        "displayName": "Corey Frang",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I decided to use it for a \"tabbed menu\".  Each of the tabs was originally developed as its own action, but then I wrote another page that just calls the individual actions.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gnarf",
                        "name": "gnarf",
                        "displayName": "Corey Frang",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-28T11:42:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-28T11:42:23.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31448",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Uhm, do you know Zend_Navigation, Corey?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dasprid",
                        "name": "dasprid",
                        "displayName": "Ben Scholzen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-28T12:55:43.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-28T12:55:43.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31453",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gnarf",
                        "name": "gnarf",
                        "displayName": "Corey Frang",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "That still doesn't actually render the content of all the tabs to the HTML (which is what I intend to do - using jQuery to tabSwitch)  I suppose a partial view helper would work as well, but some of these actions build up forms, etc. for editing - Perhaps the Action is not the place to build the form? \n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gnarf",
                        "name": "gnarf",
                        "displayName": "Corey Frang",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-28T17:40:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-28T17:40:03.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31454",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It probably isn't. Would you mind moving this discussion to a mailinglist, forum, or irc?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-28T17:43:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-28T17:43:18.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32290",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=saphir2k",
                        "name": "saphir2k",
                        "displayName": "Thorsten Ruf",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "In my opinion, Dolf is right. Move this discussion to the mailinglist. \n\nPersonaly i avoid using the action view helper, because of the very big dispatch overhead. Better remove it and talk about a smaller and faster solution. Just my two cents.\n\nThere are a lot of discussions in Blogs, Forums and Chats with the topic \"reusable content\" or \"widget problem\".  Every discussion leads to a \"new\" solution. I'am wondering a lot that the manual is missing this important topic.\n\nHopefully we will see a clear solution in 2.0.  :-)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=saphir2k",
                        "name": "saphir2k",
                        "displayName": "Thorsten Ruf",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-06-30T00:28:07.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-06-30T00:28:07.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49118",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Is there any reason to keep this issue open?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
